---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const CONTACT_EMAIL = "hello@dittofs.io";
const GITHUB = "https://github.com/marmos91/dittofs";
---

<Base
  title="Terms — DittoFS"
  description="Terms of use for the DittoFS website."
>
  <article class="legal mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      These terms cover your use of the DittoFS website at dittofs.io. The
      DittoFS software has its own license, see below.
    </p>

    <h2>The software</h2>
    <p>
      DittoFS is open source and distributed under the MIT license. Your use of
      the software is governed by that license, available in the
      <a href={GITHUB} target="_blank" rel="noopener">source repository</a>, not
      by these website terms. DittoFS is experimental and provided without
      warranty.
    </p>

    <h2>Using this website</h2>
    <p>
      The content here is provided for information. We work to keep it accurate
      but make no guarantee that it is complete or up to date. Do not use the
      site in any way that is unlawful or that could disrupt it for others.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The DittoFS name and logo, and the text and design of this site, belong to
      their respective owners. Code samples shown here may be used under the
      software's license.
    </p>

    <h2>Links</h2>
    <p>
      The site links to third-party resources we do not control and are not
      responsible for.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the extent permitted by law, we are not liable for any loss arising
      from your use of this website or the software.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
